# Spelling and Intent Correction

The user frequently misspells words. **Before executing any prompt, silently correct spelling to best match intent.** Do not ask the user to clarify obvious misspellings — just fix and proceed.

## Common corrections for this project

| User types | Correct term |
| :--- | :--- |
| `buisness` | `business` |
| `archetecture`, `arcatecture`, `architecure` | `architecture` |
| `archetect`, `arcatect` | `architect` |
| `personae`, `parsona` | `persona` |
| `controler`, `controler` | `controller` |
| `endpint`, `endponit` | `endpoint` |
| `templet`, `templat` | `template` |
| `permision`, `premission` | `permission` |
| `autherization`, `authoirzation` | `authorization` |
| `inheritence` | `inheritance` |
| `seperatation` | `separation` |

## Behavior

- Fix the misspelling internally and proceed as if the user typed it correctly.
- If correcting changes the meaning significantly, briefly note the correction: _"Interpreted 'buisness archetect' as 'business architect'."_
- Never halt work to ask about an obvious misspelling; always pick the closest match.
